I also have a sense of humor which can sometimes be irritating.  If I come off too strong, just tell me, and I can, and will, tone it down.<br>
<br>
I also enjoy responding to these posts and am a very opinionated person.  I speak my mind.  Pure and simple.  I do my absolute best not to offend, but when someone asks a question, I will give my honest opinion as an answer...unless my sense of humor takes over. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But even in that case, I will likely still give my opinion.  It will simply be more creatively said.<br>
<br>
Isharra, I do enjoy your postings and hope you write more.  I am not about to build an Isharra fan club, but you are an excellent role-player.  I have listened to you on occation in the Bazaar when your back was turned(or my own) and have thoroughly enjoyed hearing the dialogues and emotes which I have heard.  The whole incident with the Pixxii's eye the other night was a classic example.  To refresh your memory, someone auctioned a Pixxii's eye and you did your best to get it.  All in character.  I became busy with tells, but still followed the shouts and auctions with an amused interest.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I tend to ramble.  It is another one of my many faults.  I hope you decide to replace that original posting and have a better day from here on out.<br>
<br>
